# aws_ssm_assume_role — Connection Plugin

Drop-in extension of `amazon.aws.aws_ssm` with transparent **STS AssumeRole** support.

## Installation

```
your_collection/
└── plugins/
    └── connection/
        └── aws_ssm_assume_role.py   ← place the file here
```

Or use a standalone collection path and point `ansible.cfg` to it:

```ini
[defaults]
collections_path = ./collections
connection_plugins = ./plugins/connection
```

## Required IAM permissions (controller identity)

```json
{
  "Effect": "Allow",
  "Action": "sts:AssumeRole",
  "Resource": "arn:aws:iam::TARGET_ACCOUNT:role/YOUR_ROLE"
}
```

All permissions needed to actually USE SSM + S3 must be attached to the **assumed role**, not the controller identity.

---

## Usage

### Option A — per-host vars (inventory)

```yaml
# inventory/host_vars/i-0abc123def456.yml
ansible_connection: aws_ssm_assume_role
ansible_aws_ssm_bucket_name: my-ansible-bucket
ansible_aws_ssm_region: us-east-1
ansible_aws_ssm_role_arn: arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/ansible-ssm-role
ansible_aws_ssm_role_session_name: ansible-prod-session   # optional
ansible_aws_ssm_role_duration_seconds: 3600               # optional, default 3600
```

### Option B — playbook vars

```yaml
- name: Collect Linux version via SSM + AssumeRole
  hosts: all
  vars:
    ansible_connection: aws_ssm_assume_role
    ansible_aws_ssm_bucket_name: my-ansible-bucket
    ansible_aws_ssm_region: us-east-1
    ansible_aws_ssm_role_arn: arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/ansible-ssm-role

  tasks:
    - name: Get Linux version
      setup:
        gather_subset: [distribution]

    - debug:
        msg: "{{ ansible_distribution }} {{ ansible_distribution_version }}"
```

### Option C — environment variables

```bash
export ANSIBLE_AWS_SSM_ROLE_ARN=arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/ansible-ssm-role
export ANSIBLE_AWS_SSM_ROLE_SESSION_NAME=ansible-session
ansible-playbook site.yml
```

---

## Behaviour matrix

| `role_arn` set? | Behaviour |
|---|---|
| No | Identical to `amazon.aws.aws_ssm` — zero overhead |
| Yes | Calls `sts:AssumeRole` once per connection object, injects temp creds into ALL boto3 clients |

---

## Troubleshooting

| Error | Likely cause |
|---|---|
| `ImportError: amazon.aws` | Run `ansible-galaxy collection install amazon.aws` |
| `sts:AssumeRole failed [AccessDenied]` | Controller identity lacks `sts:AssumeRole` on the target role ARN |
| `Unable to locate credentials` | Assumed role credentials not propagated — check `role_arn` var name |
| `NoCredentialsError` before assume_role | No base credentials on the controller node |